cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 

- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper presents an implementation of Multipath TCP (MPTCP) under the NS-3 network simulator, which is commonly used for network research and simulation. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as MPTCP is designed to improve the security and robustness of TCP in variable network conditions. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve hardware implementation or optimization of MPTCP. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper discusses congestion control mechanisms between subflows in MPTCP. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve information theory concepts related to network performance and optimization.
